browser-->server: HTTP POST https://studies.cs.helsinki.fi/exampleapp/new_note_spa

note over browser:
The JavaScript in spa.js is dealing with with everything simultaneously,
without needing a response from the server to update the page.

On submit of the form in the HTML, the default action is prevented
(no redirect).

Then a new note is added to the DOM directly using redrawNotes().

Following this, the note is sent to the server using sendToServer().
end note

server-->browser: Status code 201, acknowledging new note was added to the server

note over browser:
Above all, the browser continues without waiting for a response from the server
at each step when compared to the example/notes page.
end note:
